Consumer groups are worried that the TPP could lower Japan’s standards on genetically modified foods, food additives and pesticide residue in line with foreign rules. They say a relaxation of standards could undermine food safety in Japan. Other countries have pointed to Japanese safety standards being used essentially as a form of non-tariff barrier to trade.
